# Code owners for OpenTheOne
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Every PR is auto-requested for review by the listed owners. The last matching
# pattern wins, so put more specific rules below more general ones.
#
# We point at the org-level @opentheone/maintainers team so reviewer routing
# survives membership changes; create the team in the GitHub org settings
# before merging this file or CODEOWNERS will silently no-op.

# Default: everything goes to the maintainers team.
*                                       @opentheone/maintainers

# CI / release infra needs an extra pair of eyes — easy to break silently.
/.github/                               @opentheone/maintainers
/Dockerfile                             @opentheone/maintainers
/docker-compose.yml                     @opentheone/maintainers
/Makefile                               @opentheone/maintainers

# Security-sensitive surfaces.
/backend/internal/auth/                 @opentheone/maintainers
/backend/internal/crypto/               @opentheone/maintainers
/backend/internal/middleware/           @opentheone/maintainers
/SECURITY.md                            @opentheone/maintainers

# Protocol layer: any change here must be cross-checked against the official
# Tencent ClawBot / iLink docs.
/backend/internal/ilink/                @opentheone/maintainers
